Both in the single-session and repeated session groups, no significant difference was determined between the 810 nm and 940 nm groups in terms of the mean VAS scores at each measuring time point (p>0.05 for all;
Figure 2
).

There was no significant difference between the single-session and repeated session groups in terms of the mean VAS scores (p>0.05 for application at 810 nm and p>0.05 for application at 940 nm;
Figure 3
).

On the postoperative Day 2 and Day 7, we did not observe significant difference between the 810 nm and 940 nm groups in terms of mean maximum mouth opening measured before the surgery (p>0.05 for each;
Figure 4
), both for the single-session and repeated session groups. Also, we did not find significant difference between the single-session and repeated session groups in terms of maximum mouth opening (p>0.05 for application at 810 nm and p>0.05 for application at 940 nm;
Figure 3
).

No significant differences was observed between the 810 nm and 940 nm groups in terms of the mean degree of swelling measured on the postoperative Day 2 and Day 7 both for the single-session and repeated session groups (p>0.05 for all;
Figure 5
). No significant difference was determined between the single-session and repeated session groups in terms of the mean degree of swelling (p>0.05 for application at 810 nm and p>0.05 for application at 940 nm;
Figure 3
).
